Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.64,0:00:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, Zecora!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.94,0:00:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I never would have found the\Ncrisscross moss without you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.44,0:00:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Of course! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.54,0:00:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} I know where it grows{\i0}\N{\i1} so it's not much to ask.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.55,0:00:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Though retrieving it has{\i0}\N{\i1} been a difficult task.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.99,0:00:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but the oxen visiting\NSweetfeather Sanctuary
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.69,0:00:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,next week will surely\Nappreciate it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.02,0:00:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It really adds a\Nshine to their coat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.49,0:00:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} There we go. Now, that{\i0}\N{\i1} wasn't so tough.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.43,0:00:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Fluttershy tell me,{\i0}\N{\i1} will this be enough?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.94,0:00:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Gee, I don't know, it's\Na pretty big pack,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.37,0:00:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so maybe enough to\Nfill up this sack?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.08,0:00:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] [giggle] Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.51,0:00:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're rubbing\Noff on me, Zecora!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.32,0:00:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! [shouts]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.79,0:00:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, oh no, oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.99,0:00:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Zecora! Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.09,0:01:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} No need to fret,{\i0}\N{\i1} I only got wet...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.36,0:01:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} At least now I can easily grab{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.63,0:01:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} all the crisscross moss{\i0}\N{\i1} there is to be had!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.01,0:01:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp]\NWhat's happening to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.71,0:01:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Honestly, it's hard to tell,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.42,0:01:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} but suddenly I{\i0}\N{\i1} don't feel so well.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.90,0:02:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, Zecora,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.57,0:02:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,let's have a listen to\Nthe ol' ticker!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.47,0:02:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [jazz drumming] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.04,0:02:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [jazz drumming] ♪{\i0}\NHmmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.72,0:02:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [jazz drumming] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.42,0:02:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [jazz drumming] ♪{\i0}\NHmmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.23,0:02:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ [jazz drumming] ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.87,0:02:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think it's\Nserious, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.11,0:02:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that wasn't a good sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.71,0:02:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe a\N{\i1} flower{\i0} did this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.05,0:02:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I take back thinking\Nit was pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.22,0:02:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We're looking for any\Ncolor other than red.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.33,0:02:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Phew!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.93,0:02:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! It's just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.04,0:02:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid you have a very rare\Ndisease called ...Swamp Fever!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.78,0:02:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Tell me, Doctor,{\i0}\N{\i1} what should I do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.48,0:03:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} I've never heard of{\i0}\N{\i1} Swamp Fever, mind you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.28,0:03:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, very little is\Nknown about the disease,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.89,0:03:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,except, of course, its symptoms:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.19,0:03:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,change of coat,\Ncoughing bubbles,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.09,0:03:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,shock sneezing, confusion\Nand the last stage...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.69,0:03:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The afflicted turn\Ninto the very trees
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.36,0:03:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that drop the disease-\Nspreading flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.43,0:03:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.53,0:03:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Is there anything{\i0}\N{\i1} that can be done?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.74,0:03:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} For such a terrible{\i0}\N{\i1} conundrum?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.17,0:03:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A cure has yet to be discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.17,0:03:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Zecora.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.38,0:03:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.58,0:03:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lot to take in..
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.98,0:03:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave you\Ntwo to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.48,0:03:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Zecora, this is\Nall my fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.02,0:03:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hadn't been helping\Nme get the crisscross moss,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.15,0:03:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't have\Ngotten Swamp Fever!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.56,0:03:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.13,0:03:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Fluttershy, you{\i0}\N{\i1} are not to blame.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.60,0:03:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} These things happen,{\i0}\N{\i1} all the same.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.93,0:03:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse to accept that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.93,0:03:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There has to be{\i1} somepony{\i0}\Nwho can help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.70,0:03:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.50,0:04:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} There's a healer of legend{\i0}\N{\i1} who never would fail.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.61,0:04:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} But I only know her{\i0}\N{\i1} from ancient folk tales.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.74,0:04:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Mystical and masked,{\i0}\N{\i1} she came in the night{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.68,0:04:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} and cured everything from{\i0}\N{\i1} hoof cough to fur blight.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.05,0:04:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} What became of the{\i0}\N{\i1} healer, nopony knows,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.72,0:04:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} for she disappeared{\i0}\N{\i1} ages and ages ago.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.12,0:04:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mystical Mask, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.96,0:04:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents would tell me about\Nher whenever I was sick in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.00,0:04:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} There's so many accounts{\i0}\N{\i1} of her power to heal{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.53,0:04:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} She can't just be a legend.{\i0}\N{\i1} I think she's real.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.77,0:04:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's who we need to cure\Nyou, then I'm going to find her!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.31,0:04:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know just the\Npony who can help!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.98,0:04:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[door opens] Twilight!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.88,0:04:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[door opens] Twilight!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.98,0:04:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm so sorry\Nto bother--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.59,0:04:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,are... are you cooking?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.22,0:04:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Spike and I are\Nhaving a cook-off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.49,0:04:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,My cauliflower bites blew\Nher sweet potato muffins
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.53,0:04:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the water!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.06,0:04:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you're\Nhere, Fluttershy,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.63,0:04:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're going to need\Na second opinion about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.80,0:05:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... they're both\Ndelicious. But ...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.30,0:05:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Zecora has Swamp Fever\Nand there's no cure
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.74,0:05:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's all my fault\Nand the only pony
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.11,0:05:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,who can cure her is\Nthe Mystical Mask
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.31,0:05:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and I need your\Nhelp to find her!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.53,0:05:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight: Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.11,0:05:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So what'd she pick? The\Ncauliflower bites, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.56,0:05:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,[sigh] That's the last book\Non ancient ponies
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.06,0:05:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and still no mention of\Nthe Mystical Mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.73,0:05:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, did we check the\Nunabridged versions?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.93,0:05:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. And the books\Non rare diseases,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.80,0:05:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the books on rare plants
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.24,0:05:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the entire section\Non bog habitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.97,0:05:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we might have to look\Nthrough every book
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.21,0:05:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in the entire library, but I\Nknow we'll figure it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.11,0:05:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.29,0:05:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, another dead end...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.62,0:05:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you found\Nanything yet, Twilight?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.43,0:05:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[snoring]\N-Twilight?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.66,0:06:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! [crash]
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.59,0:06:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness, are you OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.96,0:06:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,[sigh] I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.03,0:06:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy, you know that\NI want to help Zecora.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.77,0:06:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think we'd be a lot better\Noff if we got some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.77,0:06:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been at this for hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.87,0:06:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.68,0:06:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize how\Nlate it had gotten!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.51,0:06:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.48,0:06:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll grab you\Na pillow and--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.65,0:06:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no no no, I meant\N{\i1} you{\i0} should sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.28,0:06:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't rest until\NZecora is healed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.55,0:06:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand how you feel, but I\Nstill think we'd have more luck
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.86,0:06:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,if we tried again\Nin the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.79,0:06:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Just promise me you'll\Ntake a break soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.29,0:06:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.33,0:06:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, Fluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.20,0:06:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,[mumbling] 9 by 13 inch pan...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.87,0:06:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.11,0:06:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-stick pans!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.01,0:06:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,[sigh] What's all the commotion\Nin here, ladies?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.34,0:06:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry! But I figured out\Nwho the Mystical Mask is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.65,0:06:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] You did?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.42,0:06:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All I had to do was\Ncross-reference
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.95,0:06:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a book about masks\Nwith another book
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.52,0:06:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,on ancient\NEquestrian healers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.99,0:07:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,then use a third book\Nto translate it all
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.72,0:07:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,from Old Ponish\Nand there it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.46,0:07:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Zecora was right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.73,0:07:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mystical Mask\Nwasn't just a legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.23,0:07:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mystical Mask\Nwas MAGE MEADOWBROOK!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.00,0:07:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The ancient sorceress\Nfrom Hayseed Swamp?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.47,0:07:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We studied her at\NCelestia's school.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.67,0:07:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.94,0:07:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.31,0:07:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mage Meadowbrook wasn't\Njust a sorceress,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.44,0:07:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,she was also a\Nhealer and back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,healers wore masks so they\Nwouldn't get sick themselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.01,0:07:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy, I am so\Nincredibly proud of you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.18,0:07:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for using your research\Nskills to figure this out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.32,0:07:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But... Meadowbrook\Nlived ages ago and...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.49,0:07:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't she disappear?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.09,0:07:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm hm. But if we go\Nto Hayseed Swamp,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.16,0:07:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe we can find\Nsomething she left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.99,0:07:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that could\Nlead to a cure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.93,0:07:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like a long shot,\Nbut I guess it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.23,0:07:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to try! I've got\Nour route all planned out
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.60,0:07:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and on the way we can\Ncheck up on Zecora and--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.54,0:07:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, whoa, whoa.\NWe're leaving{\i1} now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.34,0:07:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.14,0:07:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Every second we spend waiting,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.61,0:07:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is a second Zecora\Nis coughing bubbles!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.15,0:08:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But Fluttershy,\Nyou haven't slept.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.15,0:08:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's a long journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.75,0:08:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no use trying to talk\Nme out of this, Twilight!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.99,0:08:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got no\Ntime to waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.85,0:08:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we at least\Ngrab some breakfast!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.36,0:08:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I packed cauliflower bites.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.96,0:08:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Aww. No sweet\Npotato muffins?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.70,0:08:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I.. uh.. ate them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.33,0:08:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They were actually\Nreally good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.44,0:08:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,...and that's when I\Nrealized the Mystical Mask
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.84,0:08:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,was actually Mage\NMeadowbrook!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.14,0:08:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,[cough]\N{\i1} That's marvelous, Fluttershy!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.08,0:08:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} I am quite impressed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.88,0:08:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} While you're gone{\i0}\N{\i1} on your journey{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.52,0:08:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll try not to be{\i0} ...{\i1} worried.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.42,0:08:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] Oh, no! Zecora,\Nyou didn't rhyme!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.29,0:08:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be getting worse!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.09,0:08:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Oh! No, no, no! Not at all...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.09,0:08:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Something, something... ball?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.20,0:08:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Achoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.77,0:08:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.14,0:08:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to go now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.44,0:08:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Lead the way, Fluttershy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.59,0:09:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So... where do you think\NMeadowbrook lived?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.06,0:09:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,[yawn] I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.70,0:09:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe there's\Nsomepony we can ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.27,0:09:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we might be\Nthe only ponies here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.57,0:09:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! I recognize that tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.41,0:09:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Yes, this has to be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.68,0:09:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like the\Nillustrations of her home!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.39,0:09:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Anypony who lives in\Na tree is OK by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.86,0:09:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Phew!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.99,0:09:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if the doorway\Nis sealed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.20,0:09:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we just have\Nto dig our way in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.07,0:10:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Back up, Twilight; I don't\Nwant you to get hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.10,0:10:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Or we could try\Nthe handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.61,0:10:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It really blends\Nin with the bark.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.01,0:10:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy to miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.35,0:10:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, it looks like this place\Nhas been abandoned for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.82,0:10:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] Twilight! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.76,0:10:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same kind of lily pad\Nthat gave Zecora Swamp Fever!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.46,0:10:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. I wonder if Meadowbrook\Nwas looking for a cure
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.60,0:10:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for Swamp Fever too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.10,0:10:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] Do you think she found it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.43,0:10:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope so. But let's not\Nget ahead of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.54,0:10:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly what\NI'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.64,0:10:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're making your excited\Nsqueaking noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.21,0:10:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, I wasn't making my\Nexcited squeaking noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.45,0:10:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahhhhhhhhhh!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.62,0:10:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Y'all can stop screaming now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.72,0:10:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't mean to scare ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.36,0:10:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I do that a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.19,0:10:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Scare ponies?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.26,0:11:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Or rock creepily in the dark?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.29,0:11:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well.. both, I s'pose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.06,0:11:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Name's Cattail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.57,0:11:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.17,0:11:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, but um, may I ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.07,0:11:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,why are you in Mage\NMeadowbrook's home?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.37,0:11:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I take care of the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.91,0:11:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I ain't much of a cleaner but..
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.64,0:11:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,from what I hear,\Nmy kin wasn't either,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.15,0:11:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so I doubt they'd mind a few\Ncobwebs in our ancestral home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.28,0:11:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] You're related to\NMage Meadowbrook?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.49,0:11:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.35,0:11:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my goodness,\NTwilight, we did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.52,0:11:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only did we find Mage\NMeadowbrook's old house,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.19,0:11:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we actually found one\Nof her descendants!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.83,0:11:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I would\Nnot have guessed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.40,0:11:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you lookin' for\Nsome kind of cure, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.13,0:11:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, I know\NMeadowbrook was known
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.90,0:11:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to always be writing\Nin her journals.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.11,0:11:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If she had the cure you want,\NI reckon that's where it'd be.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.58,0:11:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! I'll show\Nya the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.31,0:11:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Library? Now\Nwe're talking!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.85,0:12:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Well, libraries come\Nin all shapes and sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.26,0:12:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.52,0:12:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll take us less time\Nto go through everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.73,0:12:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Today my mom made me eat peas.{\i0}\N{\i1} Peas are yucky."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.97,0:12:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And... we can probably\Nskip this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.97,0:12:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless she found a cure\Nwhen she was a foal...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.97,0:12:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} "I met a colt today.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.57,0:12:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} He pulled my mane so I{\i0}\N{\i1} put a frog on his head."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.71,0:12:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Also not helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.14,0:12:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do kind of want to\Nsee where it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.83,0:12:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.42,0:12:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, listen to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.22,0:12:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Today, I tried again to{\i0}\N{\i1}brew an un-sniffle elixir...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.42,0:12:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} " ... and I finally{\i0}\N{\i1} got it right!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.19,0:12:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Achoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.30,0:12:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Meadowbrook, I think\Nit's time you had this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.27,0:12:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] My very own\Nhealer's mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.14,0:12:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I'm\Nready, Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.88,0:12:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.72,0:13:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] What caused this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.65,0:13:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Mother calls it "Swamp Fever".{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.12,0:13:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} We've been trying to find a{\i0}\N{\i1} cure, but it hasn't been easy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.33,0:13:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} The fever's spread{\i0}\N{\i1} like wild fire.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.11,0:13:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} I fear if we don't{\i0}\N{\i1} find the cure soon,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.04,0:13:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} everypony will be{\i0}\N{\i1} in grave danger...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.88,0:13:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} With mother sick, I didn't{\i0}\N{\i1} think I'd ever find a cure,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.09,0:13:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} but staring at those{\i0}\N{\i1} cursed flowers today.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.23,0:13:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} I saw something...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.77,0:13:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] Flash Bees!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.80,0:14:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} I realized the flower's poison{\i0}\N{\i1} didn't affect the Flash Bees{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.98,0:14:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} and if they were{\i0}\N{\i1} immune to Swamp Fever,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.21,0:14:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} their honey could be the cure!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.27,0:14:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} But they were so aggressive{\i0}\N{\i1} defending their hive,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.98,0:14:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} I didn't know how I{\i0}\N{\i1} was going to get it!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.05,0:14:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Here goes nothin'!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.49,0:14:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Today I cured Mother and{\i0}\N{\i1} the rest of the bayou.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.36,0:14:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} It was the greatest feeling{\i0}\N{\i1} I've ever experienced{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.30,0:14:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} and I promise to{\i0}\N{\i1} dedicate my life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.16,0:15:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} to curing ponies all{\i0}\N{\i1} over Equestria.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.07,0:15:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Cattail: And she did just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.30,0:15:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Right up till she\Ndisappeared without a trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.57,0:15:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So all we have to do is find\Nthose aggressive Flash Bees
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.71,0:15:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and get them to give\Nus their honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.81,0:15:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, it doesn't\Nsay how she did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.52,0:15:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Is my mane messy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.49,0:15:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I haven't slept\Nin a while but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.82,0:15:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] Oh, no! I've caught\NSwamp Fever!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.60,0:15:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.87,0:15:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure these\Nare necessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.98,0:15:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.81,0:15:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, are you sure\Nthese are necessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.01,0:15:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,YES! I won't risk\Ninfecting you or Cattail.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.85,0:15:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What you can't risk\Nis getting any sicker.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.25,0:15:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't rest, your\Nsymptoms will only get worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.06,0:16:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hm. You really should rest\Nup before going up
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.03,0:16:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,against those\NFlash Bees.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.16,0:16:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They are nasty critters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.47,0:16:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, you don't know\Nthis about me,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.37,0:16:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm pretty\Ngood with animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.84,0:16:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And besides, Dogtail...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.04,0:16:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Cattail.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.71,0:16:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, Zecora is counting on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.01,0:16:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to help her just like\NMeadowbrook helped her mother
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.95,0:16:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and all those bayou\Nponies long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.35,0:16:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But Fluttershy, as\Nmuch as Meadowbrook
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.52,0:16:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,took care of other ponies,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.19,0:16:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure she also\Ntook care of herself!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.49,0:16:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to\Nchange my mind, Twilight!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.49,0:16:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh. For being sick, she\Nsure is strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.56,0:16:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Cattail: The Flash Bee\Nhive is just up yonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.77,0:16:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you don't\Nwant me to come with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.97,0:16:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's too\Ndangerous, Twilight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.51,0:16:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I've already\Ngotten one friend hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.47,0:16:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let it\Nhappen to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.71,0:16:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Phew. OK, Fluttershy.\NYou can do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.29,0:17:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind over matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.81,0:17:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Flash Bees!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.74,0:17:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hoping I could\Nget some of your honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.21,0:17:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.72,0:17:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't let others have any.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.25,0:17:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm sorry, but\NI{\i1} really{\i0} need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.69,0:17:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh. I didn't want it to\Nhave to come to this
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.36,0:17:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'll just have to use...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.39,0:17:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The Stare.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.97,0:17:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You really are\Naggressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.41,0:18:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.02,0:18:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh. What happened? Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.19,0:18:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. I'm so glad you're OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.83,0:18:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still in\NMeadowbrook's tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.56,0:18:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You fainted but Twilight shot\Nsome magic up and caught ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.70,0:18:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It was crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.23,0:18:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness gracious!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.90,0:18:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you heard from Zecora?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.37,0:18:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.91,0:18:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.74,0:18:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We got word your zebra friend\Nhas started sprouting leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.25,0:18:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She's already\Nturning into a tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.88,0:18:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we'd\Nhave more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.68,0:18:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, you've been\Nasleep for three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.65,0:18:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Three days!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.02,0:18:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.82,0:18:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You were asleep so long, we were\Nafraid you wouldn't be able
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.19,0:18:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to move when you woke up,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.66,0:18:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but thankfully you just\Nwore yourself down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.23,0:18:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.10,0:18:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to get\Nback to the hive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.67,0:18:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I've wasted so much time-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.30,0:18:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now hang on there,\NFluttershy,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.64,0:18:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,those Flash Bee\Ncritters are tricky.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.91,0:19:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Cattail's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.17,0:19:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't even use magic\Nto calm them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.54,0:19:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have to find another\Nway to get the honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.58,0:19:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We've tried everything\Nfrom disguises
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.55,0:19:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to things I won't\Neven speak of.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.42,0:19:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been through a lot\Nthese past three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.32,0:19:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.25,0:19:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,disguises...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.26,0:19:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.17,0:19:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how she did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.47,0:19:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how Meadowbrook\Ngot the honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.41,0:19:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} This{\i0} is how Meadowbrook got\Nthe honey from the Flash Bees.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.11,0:19:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She threw a mask at 'em?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.18,0:19:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't recommend that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.28,0:19:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No. The male bees aren't\Naggressive around the queen bee
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.79,0:19:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and this mask has the same\Nstripes that she does!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.06,0:19:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy, that's brilliant!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.76,0:19:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A-A-Achoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.23,0:19:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.93,0:19:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no time to waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.66,0:19:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooves crossed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.13,0:20:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, golly, I can't watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.51,0:20:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind over matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.02,0:20:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.69,0:20:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's working!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.80,0:20:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I think she's cured\Nnow, Fluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.61,0:20:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Oh, I do feel fine,\N{\i1} and this honey is divine{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.51,0:20:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're\Nrhyming again!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.78,0:20:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back,\Nmy friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.12,0:20:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Thank you Fluttershy,{\i0}\N{\i1} for all you endured.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.02,0:20:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} If not for you, I{\i0}\N{\i1} would not be cured.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.39,0:20:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.. If it wasn't for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.56,0:21:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't have been\Nsick in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.70,0:21:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Regret is not what{\i0}\N{\i1} you should feel,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.20,0:21:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} because on this journey,{\i0}\N{\i1} you've learned a great deal.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.70,0:21:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.10,0:21:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I certainly learned that if you\Ndon't take care of yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.97,0:21:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't be able to take\Ncare of anypony else.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.64,0:21:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, if I had rested, like\NTwilight suggested all along,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.01,0:21:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe I would have thought to\Nuse Meadowbrook's mask sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.15,0:21:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell me you\Nfound the cure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.22,0:21:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Achoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.81,0:21:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Achoo!
